Former Arsenal captain, Cesc Fabregas, has reacted to Uruguay striker, Luis Suarez, joining Brazilian Serie A side Gremio. DAILY POST reports that Suarez joined Gremio on a free transfer on Saturday. The 35-year-old will remain at the club until the end of 2024. Suarez returned to his first club Nacional in July 2022 and stayed for three months. “Preparing for this beautiful challenge at Gremio, I’m excited to be there and enjoy it,” Suarez wrote on Instagram after completing his move to the Brazilian outfit. Responding to Suarez’s post, Fabregas wished the former Atletico Madrid and Barcelona attacker the best of luck at his new club. The former Chelsea midfielder wrote: “Best of luck, kid!”